docs.abstract: Thousands turned out Saturday to criticize the separation and detention of migrant families who crossed the border together.
docs.snippet: Thousands turned out Saturday to criticize the separation and detention of migrant families who crossed the border together.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Protesters marched into Lafayette Square opposite the White House on Saturday and chanted “families belong together” to counter President Trump’s “zero tolerance” immigration policy, and were joined in declaring that message by dozens of other rallies from New York to California. While the occupant of the White House was away for the weekend at his Bedminster, N.J., golf club, images of the rallies were broadcast by cable news networks throughout the day.
